00036 /* include numbertype and aid for 3.2   S. Xu   */
00037 /* structure to hold SDG info */
00038 typedef struct DFSsdg
00039   {
00040       DFdi        data;         /* tag/ref of data in file */
00041       intn        rank;         /* number of dimensions */
00042       int32 *dimsizes;    /* dimensions of data */
00043       char *coordsys;
00044       char *dataluf[3];   /* label/unit/format of data */
00045       char **dimluf[3];   /* label/unit/format for each dim */
00046       uint8 **dimscales;  /* scales for each dimension */
00047       uint8       max_min[16];  /* max, min values of data, */
00048       /*  currently atmost 8 bytes each   */
00049       int32       numbertype;   /* default is float32      */
00050       uint8       filenumsubclass;  /* number format in the file, default is IEEE */
00051       int32       aid;          /* access id     */
00052       int32       compression;  /* 0 -- not compressed  */
00053       int32       isndg;        /* 0 -- pure sdg, written by 3.1 else ndg */
00054       float64     cal, cal_err; /* calibration multiplier stuff          */
00055       float64     ioff, ioff_err;   /* calibration offset stuff              */
00056       int32       cal_type;     /* number type of data after calibration */
00057       uint8       fill_value[DFSD_MAXFILL_LEN];     /* fill value if any specified  */
00058       intn        fill_fixed;   /* whether ther fill value is a fixed value, or it can change */
00059   }
00060 DFSsdg;
00061 
00062 /* DFnsdgle is the internal structure which stores SDG or NDS and   */
00063 /* related SDG in an HDF file.                                      */
00064 /* It is a linked list.                                             */
00065 
00066 typedef struct DFnsdgle
00067   {
00068       DFdi        nsdg;         /* NDG from 3.2 or SDG from 3.1  */
00069       DFdi        sdg;          /* Only special NDF has values in this field */
00070       struct DFnsdgle *next;
00071   }
00072 DFnsdgle;
00073 
00074 typedef struct DFnsdg_t_hdr
00075   {
00076       uint32      size;
00077       DFnsdgle   *nsdg_t;
00078   }
00079 DFnsdg_t_hdr;
